This paper discusses membership inference attacks on machine learning models, which is a topic related to security and privacy in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of pre-trained models and the effectiveness of differential privacy, which are topics related to machine learning and data privacy. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper mentions the impact of data skewness on membership inference vulnerability, which is a topic related to computer vision and image classification. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible category.
